summary: breath217 replied to your ask:’Sorry to bother but could you explain me a little bit of the fake arya...’ So you think Sansa...
body:
breath217 replied to your ask:’Sorry to bother but could you explain me a little bit of the fake arya…’

So you think Sansa will ride in with the vale in the books?

Yep, I do, with a direwolf stitched onto her dress, after she’s been declared to the Vale as Sansa Stark; and that support will save Jon’s ass in the book version of the Battle of the Bastards. The situation will be the same but the context different - and therefore the dynamic they seem to be wanting in the show of ‘Sansa is bitter because Jon is King when she provided the Vale’ will actually feel natural. Because Jon won’t have rescued her and protected her from anyone. She’ll be riding up to reclaim the north and discover her brother got there before her, and the glory she was expecting will be taken away from her and given to him.

Because, as always, GRRM thinks these scenarios through in a way D&D just seem utterly stupid with smh

summary: Sansa Week is coming up fast! It’s taking place next week, from October 15-21. We hope you all participate, whether it be with...
caption:
Sansa Week is coming up fast! It’s taking place next week, from October 15-21. We hope you all participate, whether it be with art, vid, gifs, fic, graphics or whatever else strikes your fancy.

When you post your entries tag it with “sansaweek” and “sansasource” so we can reblog all your creations! If You have any questions feel free to ask. Follow one list or mix them up it’s your choice. Also, we ask that if you are making a text post for the event, you put it under a ‘read more’.

Prompt list:

  • DAY ONE: Queen or Dreams
  • DAY TWO: Family or Color
  • DAY THREE: Favorite Season/ Favorite Book or Fashion
  • DAY FOUR: Politics or Lady of Winterfell or Alayne Stone
  • DAY FIVE: Quote/Lyrics or Favourite Scene/Favourite Chapter
  • DAY SIX: Relationships or Heroes
  • DAY SEVEN: Historical Parallels or  Free Choice

question: Hi! So, I’m technically relatively new to the ASOIAF fandom (I’ve only watched the shows but read a lot of Book-only metas), and I’ve noticed that in a lot of fics Sansa holds a grudge against Robb for never trading her for Jaime. Is this a sentiment she expresses in the texts?
answer:
It is not; I don’t think Sansa even realized that was an option. (She did know that Jaime’s safety protected her safety, and vice versa.) It’s purely a fan-held resentment (which I am not immune to), projected on Sansa.

Possibly if Sansa ever finds out more about the progress of the war (from whom? the Blackfish maybe, maybe Brienne), she will gain that sentiment, but I imagine that either her uncle Brynden or Brienne would be kind enough to explain the political reasons Robb had to hold off. (Both of them would also explain that the Starks believed both Sansa and Arya were being held hostage, and Sansa would of course realize that’s why the Lannisters were never truly serious about a trade offer, as they didn’t have Arya.) And mind you, if Sansa finds out about Robb’s will – which abandoned her to the Lannisters and her marriage to Tyrion, in favor of legitimizing and making her bastard half-brother heir instead – her feelings may become very conflicted, nevertheless. (Realizing the political necessities vs the burning shame of Robb’s lack of faith in her, etc.)

But for now – the emotions Sansa expresses towards Robb during the course of the books are complete faith that he will win the war and come save her, a desire to be as brave as he is, and utter grief when he and her mother were betrayed and murdered. Even in her TWOW preview chapter she thinks of Robb as a king and a man, unlike a 17-year-old boy she meets. I hope that helps!

body:
Fanfic idea Petyr x Sansa

Imagine Sansa giving Petyr some kind of drug with his wine to test his boundaries and make him lose control. Peryr turns into a cheeky, needy and extroverted man for the night. What else might happen while he’s out of his mind?
